postcontent:
This knife is brand new in original packaging.

Reflecting the best of its Finnish heritage, the Finn Bear is an extremely affordable version of our popular Sisu. It's ideal for hunting, fishing or camping trips, and makes an efficient utility knife as well! The 4116 Krupp Stainless blade is hollow ground and given an Rc hardness of 56-57, so it will hold a good edge and is easy to re-sharpen. Its blade shape is centuries old and practical because of its good sturdy point for piercing and long belly for skinning, cutting and carving. It's big and strong enough to skin a Moose, yet thin and delicate enough to slice a tomato or cut up an apple. The Finn Bear has a straight handle with a slightly ribbed texture for traction. Its modified diamond cross section will fit your hand like a glove and accommodate a wide variety of gripping methods. title: For Sale:  M1 Rifle "Garand", Springfield Armory 1942 Production
location: Aiken, Williston, Barnwell, Orangeburg, Columbia, South Carolina
postcontent:
This AWESOME Garand was "born" in October 1942 in the nation's military armory, in Springfield, MA.  It was re-armored in 1953, for use in the Korean War.  The barrel is dated 1953, and is also Springfield.  The only two parts I can find that are not Springfield are the safety lever (H&R) and the windage knob (BME-Italy).  After Italy surrendered to the allies in WWII, they soon began building Garands themselves.  

The muzzle wear indicates very little use.  Good as new barrel condition.  The heel of the receiver is dipped in lead, which is also quite rare and collectable.

The maple stock is a military replacement, indicated by the proof marks and the Dept. of Defense cartouche on the left side.

All in all, a very nice, highly serviceable M1 Garand, that should provide years of happy shooting.

Plenty of ammunition and clips are available at a reasonable price.

I can meet face to face in the Columbia/Aiken/Barnwell/Orangeburg area.
Buyer will be non-felon, SC resident, not under indictment for a violent crime, and will have $650 in hand to receive this rifle.
